[
    {
        "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 3.42
    },
    {
        "text": " Hey, I'm Diana.",
        "start": 3.42,
        "duration": 1.06
    },
    {
        "text": "You're watching Physics Girl,\nand this is video number 3",
        "start": 4.48,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "in the series of\nriddles that I'm",
        "start": 7.26,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "asking to my friend,\nKurt Hugo Schneider, who",
        "start": 8.97,
        "duration": 2.38
    },
    {
        "text": "also happens to be a\nreally big music YouTuber.",
        "start": 11.35,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "We left off in the last\nvideo with the Broom Riddle.",
        "start": 14.07,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "So here's the setup\nfor that again.",
        "start": 16.98,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so I'm going to balance\nthis broom on my finger",
        "start": 19.35,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "so that my finger is underneath\nthe center of gravity.",
        "start": 22.29,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "For a situation like a\nnormal broom on earth,",
        "start": 25.08,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "you could either use center\nof mass or center of gravity",
        "start": 27.42,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "for this riddle.",
        "start": 29.85,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, so I'm going to\npretend that we're going",
        "start": 30.67,
        "duration": 2.36
    },
    {
        "text": "to cut the broom right here.",
        "start": 33.03,
        "duration": 1.23
    },
    {
        "text": " Right where you balance it.",
        "start": 34.26,
        "duration": 0.84
    },
    {
        "text": " Right where I balance it.",
        "start": 35.1,
        "duration": 0.68
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 35.78,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " So now you have two pieces\nof this broom, this handle part",
        "start": 36.28,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "and then the sweepy part.",
        "start": 39.42,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 40.79,
        "duration": 0.85
    },
    {
        "text": " Which of these\nsides is heavier,",
        "start": 41.64,
        "duration": 3.18
    },
    {
        "text": "or are they the same weight?",
        "start": 44.82,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "Well,",
        "start": 49.59,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " This side has to be heavier\nbecause that side goes out",
        "start": 50.09,
        "duration": 3.46
    },
    {
        "text": "so much further.",
        "start": 53.55,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, if we just imagine a\n\"broom,\" which is basically",
        "start": 54.99,
        "duration": 5.1
    },
    {
        "text": "a long stick with one\nenormously massively heavyweight",
        "start": 60.09,
        "duration": 3.929
    },
    {
        "text": "on this end, then the\nbalancing point would--",
        "start": 64.019,
        "duration": 3.861
    },
    {
        "text": "this side is always\ngoing to-- yeah,",
        "start": 67.88,
        "duration": 1.581
    },
    {
        "text": "the balancing point would\nbe very close to here.",
        "start": 69.461,
        "duration": 1.999
    },
    {
        "text": "This side is going to be\nmuch heavier, but this side--",
        "start": 71.46,
        "duration": 2.63
    },
    {
        "text": "it still balances because that\nside's so far over there, so",
        "start": 74.09,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "the torques, or whatever\nyou call it, balance out.",
        "start": 76.65,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "This side has got to be heavier.",
        "start": 78.96,
        "duration": 1.72
    },
    {
        "text": "Amazing.",
        "start": 80.68,
        "duration": 1.372
    },
    {
        "text": "You killed that, awesome.",
        "start": 82.052,
        "duration": 2.338
    },
    {
        "text": "Your reasoning was my favorite\ntype of reasoning, which",
        "start": 84.39,
        "duration": 2.339
    },
    {
        "text": "is taking the riddle\nand you're like,",
        "start": 86.729,
        "duration": 1.541
    },
    {
        "text": "let's take it to\nthe extreme, which",
        "start": 88.27,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "is like if this is super,\nsuper heavy, which obviously,",
        "start": 90.09,
        "duration": 3.93
    },
    {
        "text": "this part is heavier than\nthe rest of the broom.",
        "start": 94.02,
        "duration": 2.006
    },
    {
        "text": "That wasn't a given,\nbut if you've ever",
        "start": 96.026,
        "duration": 1.624
    },
    {
        "text": "felt a broom, what you're\nbalancing is the torques.",
        "start": 97.65,
        "duration": 3.344
    },
    {
        "text": "So what you're balancing\nis the torques,",
        "start": 100.994,
        "duration": 1.666
    },
    {
        "text": "and because the broom\ngoes so far over this way,",
        "start": 102.66,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "you get a long distance, and\nthen a little bit of mass,",
        "start": 106.26,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "and then big mass and\nshort distance over here.",
        "start": 108.66,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "But when you're\nbalancing torques,",
        "start": 111.18,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "which is distance\ntimes force, you're",
        "start": 112.66,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "not putting those gravitational\nforces in those equations",
        "start": 114.36,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "at the ends of the\nbroom, but rather, you",
        "start": 117.0,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "diagram it so that\nthe forces that",
        "start": 119.07,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "are acting on the center of\nmass of each of the sides.",
        "start": 120.49,
        "duration": 3.1
    },
    {
        "text": "Still, the distance\non the left is longer,",
        "start": 123.59,
        "duration": 2.06
    },
    {
        "text": "so that mass has to be less.",
        "start": 125.65,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "But there is a\nsituation in which",
        "start": 127.35,
        "duration": 2.06
    },
    {
        "text": "the-- let me see if I can\nget this right-- the longer",
        "start": 129.41,
        "duration": 2.38
    },
    {
        "text": "side of that cut\ncan be more massive.",
        "start": 131.79,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "So think if you can come up\nwith a situation like that.",
        "start": 135.33,
        "duration": 2.59
    },
    {
        "text": "So more specifically,\nif you've got a rod",
        "start": 137.92,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "with some distribution\nof mass, can you make it",
        "start": 139.86,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "so that when you balance your\nfinger on the center of mass",
        "start": 142.77,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "and then cut it there, this\nlonger side is actually",
        "start": 146.16,
        "duration": 3.57
    },
    {
        "text": "more massive?",
        "start": 149.73,
        "duration": 0.844
    },
    {
        "text": "If you have a guess,\nleave it in the comments.",
        "start": 150.574,
        "duration": 1.916
    },
    {
        "text": "Moving on to the next riddle.",
        "start": 152.49,
        "duration": 1.231
    },
    {
        "text": "You've already answered\nplenty of riddles,",
        "start": 153.721,
        "duration": 1.749
    },
    {
        "text": "so you might even want\npen and paper for this.",
        "start": 155.47,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": " OK, pen and paper.",
        "start": 157.95,
        "duration": 1.031
    },
    {
        "text": "Got it.",
        "start": 158.981,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 159.48,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "So I give you two\n2s, two number 2s.",
        "start": 159.979,
        "duration": 2.892
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 162.871,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "A 2 and a 2.",
        "start": 163.37,
        "duration": 1.445
    },
    {
        "text": " A 2 and a 2.",
        "start": 164.815,
        "duration": 0.585
    },
    {
        "text": " All right.",
        "start": 165.4,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " You can do anything with\nthem with pretty common math",
        "start": 165.9,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "symbols.",
        "start": 170.22,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "So for example, 2\nto the 2 would be 4.",
        "start": 170.72,
        "duration": 3.13
    },
    {
        "text": "2 plus 2 would be 4.",
        "start": 173.85,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "2 times square root\nof 2 would be--",
        "start": 175.49,
        "duration": 3.565
    },
    {
        "text": " Got it.",
        "start": 179.055,
        "duration": 0.535
    },
    {
        "text": "So 2 root 2.",
        "start": 179.59,
        "duration": 1.535
    },
    {
        "text": " So you could even do like 2.2.",
        "start": 181.125,
        "duration": 3.315
    },
    {
        "text": " Got it.",
        "start": 184.44,
        "duration": 0.54
    },
    {
        "text": "So I can also do 22.",
        "start": 184.98,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "I can concatenate them.",
        "start": 186.42,
        "duration": 1.11
    },
    {
        "text": " You can do 22.",
        "start": 187.53,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 188.58,
        "duration": 0.84
    },
    {
        "text": " So I want you to try\nand make the number 5.",
        "start": 189.42,
        "duration": 5.01
    },
    {
        "text": " Got it.",
        "start": 194.43,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": " Using two 2s.",
        "start": 195.21,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": " Just two 2s.",
        "start": 197.34,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": " Just two 2s.",
        "start": 198.24,
        "duration": 0.93
    },
    {
        "text": " All right.",
        "start": 199.17,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " The simplest.",
        "start": 199.67,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": "These are the everyday\nmathematical symbols",
        "start": 200.58,
        "duration": 2.33
    },
    {
        "text": "you're allowed to use.",
        "start": 202.91,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": " OK.",
        "start": 204.3,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": "Totally cheating if I look at\none of the 2s in the mirror",
        "start": 204.99,
        "duration": 2.375
    },
    {
        "text": "and call it a 5, right?",
        "start": 207.365,
        "duration": 1.255
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes, that is cheating.",
        "start": 208.62,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": " OK, just making sure.",
        "start": 210.75,
        "duration": 1.304
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, there you are.",
        "start": 212.054,
        "duration": 0.916
    },
    {
        "text": " Making sure.",
        "start": 212.97,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "So I'm going to put a 2 on top,\nand then take the square root,",
        "start": 215.28,
        "duration": 3.139
    },
    {
        "text": "and then take the square root,\nand then take the square root.",
        "start": 218.419,
        "duration": 2.541
    },
    {
        "text": "And then I'm going to add a\ndot, dot, dot, dot, dot, so",
        "start": 220.96,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "an infinite square root of 2.",
        "start": 223.26,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "Because that approaches 1.",
        "start": 225.33,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": " Uh-huh.",
        "start": 226.81,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": " And then divide by 0.2 for 5.",
        "start": 227.77,
        "duration": 2.66
    },
    {
        "text": "So this is really dot, dot, dot.",
        "start": 230.43,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "So this is sort of just an\ninfinite operation here.",
        "start": 232.29,
        "duration": 4.09
    },
    {
        "text": " You got around my rule.",
        "start": 236.38,
        "duration": 2.612
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, but the dot, dot,\ndot is not listed here,",
        "start": 238.992,
        "duration": 2.298
    },
    {
        "text": "and that is\ncertainly something--",
        "start": 241.29,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "Kurt, it's against the rules.",
        "start": 243.6,
        "duration": 2.825
    },
    {
        "text": "But that kind of out-of-the-box\nthinking should not be",
        "start": 246.425,
        "duration": 2.605
    },
    {
        "text": "squashed.",
        "start": 249.03,
        "duration": 0.94
    },
    {
        "text": "It should be encouraged, and so\nI applaud your solution, Kurt.",
        "start": 249.97,
        "duration": 4.65
    },
    {
        "text": "It's just there\nis a simpler way.",
        "start": 254.62,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": " There's no trick, OK.",
        "start": 256.38,
        "duration": 1.709
    },
    {
        "text": "I genuinely want\nto figure it out.",
        "start": 258.089,
        "duration": 3.151
    },
    {
        "text": "Square root of 1 over\n0.2 squared is 5.",
        "start": 261.24,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, I just need to\nget rid of the 1.",
        "start": 263.91,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Square root of 0.2\nto the negative 2.",
        "start": 265.86,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "Can I use negative?",
        "start": 267.9,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "Can I use negative 2?",
        "start": 268.79,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "That's allowed, right?",
        "start": 270.23,
        "duration": 1.09
    },
    {
        "text": " You can use negative 2.",
        "start": 271.32,
        "duration": 1.245
    },
    {
        "text": " OK, is that the solution?",
        "start": 272.565,
        "duration": 1.125
    },
    {
        "text": " That's it.",
        "start": 273.69,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": " That's it?",
        "start": 274.47,
        "duration": 0.69
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 275.16,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " That's it.",
        "start": 275.66,
        "duration": 1.265
    },
    {
        "text": "Sweet.",
        "start": 276.925,
        "duration": 0.535
    },
    {
        "text": " Yay.",
        "start": 277.46,
        "duration": 0.636
    },
    {
        "text": "That was amazing.",
        "start": 278.096,
        "duration": 0.754
    },
    {
        "text": " There's nothing\nsimpler than that.",
        "start": 278.85,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "That was a tricky one.",
        "start": 281.01,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "I have to say, that\nwas tricky right there.",
        "start": 282.39,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": " Math major right here.",
        "start": 285.3,
        "duration": 1.23
    },
    {
        "text": "I feel like you shouldn't\nbe doing only music.",
        "start": 286.53,
        "duration": 3.87
    },
    {
        "text": " Really using that math degree.",
        "start": 290.4,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "First time I've used my math\ndegree in nearly 10 years.",
        "start": 292.33,
        "duration": 4.49
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, now I'm pumped.",
        "start": 296.82,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "This one pumped me up.",
        "start": 299.34,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": " That was really good.",
        "start": 301.23,
        "duration": 1.03
    },
    {
        "text": " Now I'm thinking\nabout this one, though.",
        "start": 305.79,
        "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
        "text": " I know some of you\ncan't go on with life",
        "start": 307.93,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "without knowing what\nriddle I gave Kurt, so here",
        "start": 309.94,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "is the final bonus riddle.",
        "start": 312.02,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "I'll put the answer in\nthe description tomorrow.",
        "start": 314.11,
        "duration": 2.85
    },
    {
        "text": "I lost Kurt for about 25\nminutes because I gave him",
        "start": 316.96,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "another riddle.",
        "start": 320.56,
        "duration": 1.02
    },
    {
        "text": " I did get it.",
        "start": 321.58,
        "duration": 0.81
    },
    {
        "text": " You did get it.",
        "start": 322.39,
        "duration": 0.72
    },
    {
        "text": " But there's clearly\nsome clever rotational,",
        "start": 323.11,
        "duration": 2.95
    },
    {
        "text": "or there's some very\nintuitive way of seeing this.",
        "start": 326.06,
        "duration": 4.307
    },
    {
        "text": " I feel like I know\nwhat you're going to do",
        "start": 330.367,
        "duration": 1.833
    },
    {
        "text": "with the rest of your evening.",
        "start": 332.2,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "I give you a math\nproblem, you're like, no.",
        "start": 334.14,
        "duration": 1.791
    },
    {
        "text": "Like, hold on.",
        "start": 335.931,
        "duration": 1.099
    },
    {
        "text": "Like, just a minute.",
        "start": 337.03,
        "duration": 1.393
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm like, Kurt,\ncan we do it after.",
        "start": 338.423,
        "duration": 2.207
    },
    {
        "text": "You're like, just a minute.",
        "start": 340.63,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "This was amazing.",
        "start": 342.76,
        "duration": 0.97
    },
    {
        "text": "Thank you.",
        "start": 343.73,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " Oh no, thank you.",
        "start": 344.23,
        "duration": 1.21
    },
    {
        "text": "Thank you so much.",
        "start": 345.44,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "This was so much fun.",
        "start": 346.31,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": "This was so much fun for me.",
        "start": 347.68,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": " Thank you guys for watching.",
        "start": 348.94,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "It was a fun guest.",
        "start": 351.06,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": " And happy physicsing.",
        "start": 352.36,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah.",
        "start": 356.12,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
